## Key Concepts

### Basic App Structure

```python
import streamlit as st

st.title("My App")
st.write("Hello, world!")

# Sidebar
with st.sidebar:
    option = st.selectbox("Choose", ["A", "B", "C"])

# Main content
if option == "A":
    st.write("You selected A")
```

### Widgets

```python
# Text input
name = st.text_input("Name")

# Number input
age = st.number_input("Age", min_value=0, max_value=120)

# Slider
value = st.slider("Value", 0, 100, 50)

# Select box
choice = st.selectbox("Select", ["Option 1", "Option 2"])

# Multi-select
selected = st.multiselect("Select multiple", ["A", "B", "C"])

# File upload
file = st.file_uploader("Upload file", type=["csv", "txt"])

# Button
if st.button("Submit"):
    st.write("Submitted!")
```

### Session State

Persist values across reruns:

```python
# Initialize
if "count" not in st.session_state:
    st.session_state.count = 0

# Update
if st.button("Increment"):
    st.session_state.count += 1

st.write(f"Count: {st.session_state.count}")
```

### Caching

Prevent expensive recomputation:

```python
@st.cache_data
def load_data(path):
    return pd.read_csv(path)

@st.cache_resource
def init_model():
    return load_heavy_model()
```

